        public Cell createAndPlaceCell(Design design,
                               EDIFCell parent,
                               java.lang.String name,
                               Unisim cellType,
                               java.lang.String location)
        Creates a new cell from scratch in the logical and physical netlists and places it at the location specied.
        Parameters:
        design - The design to which to add the cell.
        parent - The parent cell to which to add this cell
        name - Name of the cell
        cellType - The Unisim library cell type
        location - The Vivado name of the site/BEL location (i.e. SLICE_X45Y42/AFF)
        Returns:
        The newly created cell or null if it could not be created or placed.

      • createAndPlaceCell

        public Cell createAndPlaceCell(Design design,
                               EDIFCell parent,
                               java.lang.String name,
                               Unisim cellType,
                               Site site,
                               ElementType element)
        Convenience function to create and place a new cell.
        Parameters:
        design - The design to add the cell to
        parent - If set to null, the EDIFCellInstance will not reference the netlist.
        name - Name of the cell
        cellType - The Unisim library cell
        site - The site onto which to place this cell
        element - The BEL site onto which to place this cell
        Returns:
        the newly created cell.
